divs: sighting details20+ red-orange orbs were going ne to west slowly at about 200-300 ft over weston fl around 12:15-12:30 am 1\1\13. they were going ne to west slowly at about 200-300 ft. i believed they may have been chinese lanterns, but there was absolutely no wind, which rules that out. airplanes, both commercial and private and helicopters flew close enough to rule out that type of confusion. i've attached a picture, however, not very clear since it was taken with my cell phone w\o flash. i have more pics if anyone wants to analyze them.
